### Orifice Sizing

The injector orifice area required for each propellant is given by:

$$A = \frac{\dot{m}}{C_d \sqrt{2 \rho \Delta P}}$$

**Known values:**

$$\dot{m}(\mathrm{N_2O}) = 0.01339\,\mathrm{kg/s}$$

$$\dot{m}(\mathrm{Ethanol}) = 0.00669\,\mathrm{kg/s}$$

$$C_d = 0.7$$

$$\rho(\mathrm{N_2O}\ \text{at room temperature}) = 745\,\mathrm{kg/m^3}$$

$$\rho(\mathrm{Ethanol}\ \text{at room temperature}) = 789\,\mathrm{kg/m^3}$$

$$\Delta P = 1000\,\mathrm{psi} - 700\,\mathrm{psi} = 2.068 \times 10^6\,\mathrm{Pa}$$

**Results:**

$$A(\mathrm{N_2O}) = 3.446 \times 10^{-7}\,\mathrm{m^2} \rightarrow 0.664\,\mathrm{mm}\ \text{diameter}$$

$$A(\mathrm{Ethanol}) = 1.673 \times 10^{-7}\,\mathrm{m^2} \rightarrow 0.460\,\mathrm{mm}\ \text{diameter}$$

